          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Least-squares method used to find from the decay",
                "curves the initial activity of the isotopes produced",
                "which are identified mainly by accurate half-life",
                "measurements sometimes completed by gamma spectrum",
                "measurements for better identification"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Corrections for backscattering, self-absorption,",
                "window and air absorption were required for the  beta",
                "counting. These corrections were calculated on the",
                "basis of the following references=",
                "K. Scheiser, radioactive isotope (Springer-verlag,",
                "Berlin, 1957) and K. Siegbahn, beta and gamma-ray",
                "spectroscopy (North-Holland Publ.Co, Amsterdam, 1955).",
                "For the standard, self-absorption and backscattering",
                "corrections were determined experimentally by a method",
                "described in Acta Phys. Pol. 13(1954)243.",
                "The neutron flux variations were taken into account.",
                "correction of the conversion electron emission was made",
                "on the basis of experimental or theoretical values of",
                "the conversion coefficients."
              ]
            }
